 -- Volker Theile <volker.theile@openmediavault.org>  Fri, 31 Mar 2017 20:31:36 +0200

openmediavault (3.0.68) stable; urgency=low

  * Various bug fixes and improvements.
  * Add 'omv-confdbadm exists' command.
  * Do not use /etc/fstab entries like UUID=<xxx> anymore because this
    will make problems with LV/BTRFS snapshots. Use /dev/disk/by-xxx/xxx
    device files instead.
  * Improve the datamodel to be able to resolve shared folder references.
  * File systems will be mounted according to FHS below /srv now.
  * Outsource TFTP into a plugin. Please note that the existing configuration
    will be deleted.

 -- Volker Theile <volker.theile@openmediavault.org>  Mon, 20 Mar 2017 12:38:22 +0100

